HEADWORD: Prosopulmonata
<hw>Pros`o*pul`mo*na"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/ forward + L. <ets>pulmo</ets> a lung.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of pulmonate mollusks having the
breathing organ situated on the neck, as in the common snail.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

